// Semantic direction:
// std.mønster provides regular expressions using a Thompson NFA compiled to DFA.
// mønster_kompiler parses the regex syntax and constructs the NFA.
// thompson_construction builds an NFA directly from the syntax tree.
// subset_construction converts the NFA to a DFA by tracking sets of NFA states.
// minimize_dfa merges equivalent DFA states using Hopcroft's algorithm.
// treff carries the matched text span and named/numbered group captures.
// treff_gruppe(0) is the full match; treff_gruppe(1) is the first capture group.
// navngitt_gruppe retrieves a capture group by name (defined with (?P<name>...)).
// flagg_store_bokstaver makes the match case-insensitive.
// flagg_flerlinjet makes ^ and $ match line boundaries, not just string boundaries.
// mønster_finn returns the first treff or null; mønster_finn_alle returns all non-overlapping matches.
// mønster_finn_iter is a lazy iterator that produces treff values one at a time.
// mønster_erstatt_m replaces the first match with erstatnings_mal.
// erstatt_gruppe_ref substitutes captured groups: $1 or ${name} in the replacement.
// erstatt_funksjon replaces each match by calling a user function with the treff.
// mønster_del_m splits the string at each match of the pattern.
// glob_mønster provides shell-style glob matching: * matches any run of non-separator chars.
// glob_finn_filer walks the filesystem and returns paths matching the glob.

// Primitive flow:
// mønster_kompiler("(\\d+)-(\\w+)"): parse → NFA → DFA
// mønster_finn("abc123-foo", mønster): DFA simulation → first match → treff{0:"123-foo", 1:"123", 2:"foo"}
// mønster_erstatt_m("hello WORLD", /[A-Z]+/i, "***"): find first uppercase run → replace → "*** WORLD"
// mønster_erstatt_alle_m: apply globally → "*** ***"
// glob_finn_filer("src/**/*.no"): walk src/ recursively → match *.no → return paths

// This defines the native std.mønster module: Thompson NFA, DFA minimization,
// capture groups, named groups, replacement templates, and glob patterns.
